<h3 id="doc-active-state">Active State</h3>
<p>The <code>.active</code> class visually indicates that the button is
currently selected, pressed, or toggled. It is useful for:</p>
<ul>
<li>Toggle buttons (on/off states)</li>
<li>Multi-button selections</li>
<li>Navigation highlights</li>
</ul>
<button class="btn btn-blue active mt-4">
Active
</button>
<pre class="html"><code>&lt;button class=&quot;btn btn-blue active&quot;&gt;Active&lt;/button&gt;</code></pre>
<p>Note: Make sure the button is <strong>not disabled</strong>, as
<code>:disabled</code> takes precedence over <code>.active</code>.</p>
